Communicable diseases and comorbidities have been highlighted at the tabling of the Northern Cape’s Health department budget. Health MEC Maruping Lekoene says a large chunk of the budget of R354 million has been allocated to the ongoing fight of HIV and AIDS. He says the department is also going all out to fight the threat posed by non-communicable diseases during the COVID-19 pandemic. “From a total budget of R651.3 million for the comprehensive HIV and AIDS grant an amount of R354.7 million is specifically allocated for the anti-retroviral treatment programme. We’re cautiously optimistic about progressive successes we have made in the combating of communicable diseases. “In the face of COVID-19, the threat posed by non-communicable diseases such as diabetes, hypertension and kidney diseases and cancers has been magnified”